.Im MicroEmacs command|c
.so me.tni
.TH c-slashify 3
.XI c-slashify - "C language, append backslash to end of lines of region"
.XI c-deslashify - "C language, remove backslash to end of lines of region"
.SH NAME
.Me "|c-slashify"
c-slashify \- C language, append backslash to end of lines of region
.br
.Me "|c-deslashify"
c-deslashify \- C language, remove backslash to end of lines of region
.Me $a
.SH SYNOPSIS
.na
.B c-slashify
.br
.B c-deslashify
.ad
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B c-slashify
and 
.B c-deslashify
add and remove backslash characters to the ends of line(s) defined by a 
region, respectively.
.PP
The commands are used with the C programming language for 
.C #define 
macro  editing,  allowing   backslashes  to  be  added  and  removed  quickly.
Backslashes are typically removed with 
.B c-deslashify
and the macro edited before the backslashes are re-applied
using 
.BR c-slashify .
